HeteroMerPred
A heterogeneous ensemble algorithm which is the voting of multi-expert classifiers, SVM, kNN, and RF, in the task of pre-miRNA classification. 

Web server is also available at http://bicep.kmutt.ac.th/HeteroMirPred


Install
-------
- create a ne environment via conda file (heteromerpred27.yml)
     "conda env create -n heteromerpred27 -f heteromerpred27.yml"
     "conda activate heteromerpred27"
     "cpanm Algorithm::Numerical::Shuffle"
     
- or install packages separately follows

conda install -c conda-forge/label/cf201901 openjdk=8.0.192
conda install -c bioconda viennarna
conda install -c bioconda perl-bioperl
conda install -c bioconda perl-statistics-basic
cpanm Algorithm::Numerical::Shuffle

Run example 
-------

[HeteroMirPred]$ perl HeteroMirPred.pl user_input.fasta
-----------


Citation
- Lertampaiporn, S., Thammarongtham, C., Nukoolkit, C., Kaewkamnerdpong, B., & Ruengjitchatchawalya, M. (2013). Heterogeneous ensemble approach with discriminative features and modified-SMOTEbagging for pre-miRNA classification. Nucleic acids research, 41(1), e21-e21.
